---
import Container from "./Container.astro";
import SectionLabel from "./SectionLabel.astro";
---

<section
  id="about"
  class="relative scroll-mt-24 pt-8 pb-12 md:pt-10 md:pb-14"
  aria-labelledby="about-label"
>
  <Container>
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <SectionLabel label="About" index="01" class="reveal" />

      <h2 id="about-label" class="sr-only">About</h2>

      <p
        class="reveal mt-8 text-xl leading-relaxed text-muted sm:text-2xl sm:leading-relaxed md:mt-10"
        style="--reveal-delay: 80ms"
      >
        I graduated from Inha University in Tashkent <span class="text-text font-medium">ranked first out of 337</span> in my final semester. Working across Android and Kotlin Multiplatform teams since then, I've learned that the hardest part of shipping software isn't the framework you pick — it's the careful code review, the clear module boundary, and the honest scope conversation. I work best with teammates who write code they'd want to inherit, and I try to <span class="text-text font-medium">leave every project easier to work with than I found it</span>.
      </p>

      <div
        class="reveal mt-10 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-3 text-sm text-muted"
        style="--reveal-delay: 160ms"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span
            class="grid h-6 w-6 place-items-center rounded-md border border-border/60 bg-surface/60"
          >
            <svg
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              class="h-3 w-3 text-primary"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path d="M12 2 15 9l7 .6-5.3 4.7L18 22l-6-3.5L6 22l1.3-7.7L2 9.6 9 9z" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span class="text-text font-medium">B.Sc. Computer Science</span>
          <span class="text-muted">— Inha University in Tashkent</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</section>
